  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db0\u0dad\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"No shots were fired to harm the protesters\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Army has issued a statement saying that it rejects the claims that the Army troops deliberately targeted and fired at the protesters who entered the Presidential Palace by force.",
        "The army says that the army's attention has been drawn to these allegations as videos of the army firing are being circulated on social media.",
        "It is also mentioned to the army that the army fired several shots in the sky as well as at the side wall of the main entrance gate to prevent the protesters from entering the premises.",
        "The Army further emphasizes that the shooting in the sky and on the wall of the side gate was used as a tactic to prevent the group from entering, and it was not an attempt to physically harm the blockaders."
      ],
